<p><strong>Solid Mensuration Problems with Solutions PDF</strong></p>
<p>Solid mensuration is the branch of geometry that deals with the measurement of volumes of three-dimensional shapes. Solving solid mensuration problems requires a strong understanding of geometric formulas and spatial reasoning skills.</p>
<p><strong>Problem 1:</strong></p>
<p>Find the volume of a rectangular prism with length 5 cm, width 3 cm, and height 2 cm.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Volume = Length × Width × Height
Volume = 5 cm × 3 cm × 2 cm
Volume = 30 cm³</p>
<p><strong>Problem 2:</strong></p>
<p>Find the volume of a cylinder with radius 4 cm and height 6 cm.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Volume = πr²h
Volume = π(4 cm)²(6 cm)
Volume = 96π cm³ ≈ 301.6 cm³</p>
<p><strong>Problem 3:</strong></p>
<p>Find the volume of a cone with radius 5 cm and height 8 cm.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Volume = (1/3)πr²h
Volume = (1/3)π(5 cm)²(8 cm)
Volume = (400/3)π cm³ ≈ 418.9 cm³</p>
<p><strong>Problem 4:</strong></p>
<p>Find the volume of a sphere with radius 3 cm.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Volume = (4/3)πr³
Volume = (4/3)π(3 cm)³
Volume = (36π/3) cm³
Volume = 37.7 cm³</p>
<p><strong>Problem 5:</strong></p>
<p>Find the volume of a pyramid with base length 6 cm, width 4 cm, and height 5 cm.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Volume = (1/3) × Base Area × Height
Volume = (1/3) × (6 cm × 4 cm) × 5 cm
Volume = (60/3) cm³
Volume = 20 cm³</p>